{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c1cf828-6be4-4fb9-8dd9-e0fa5652baa5","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` is listed first but depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by reordering `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ilCWQs6VDoLZaj5aBNFJ1q","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-63f3f47275494698bc55d8710b5e2713/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-63f3f47275494698bc55d8710b5e2713/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"d7334d25-d086-4fda-8986-7a3c9243bda5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear **before** them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) - opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) - defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) - opens both Domain and Services\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":458,"requestId":"F02F:1EDE:1F448CE:2353318:69F9B07C"},"id":"3fea8cc8-d450-4bf4-954b-e98ee23aac8a","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:55:32.535Z","parentId":"a6708485-1334-47df-af19-5fa93c96c69d"}
